The Federal Capital Territory (FCT) Police Command has arrested about a dozen kidnappers in Abuja. Intelligence indicted them for the recent abductions that occurred at the Kwali and Bwari areas. They also carried out attacks at Tungan Maje community, a suburb in the nationâ€™s capitals. The criminals were nabbed during a three-day undercover operation by a Police crack team. The multiple raids combed the forests and hideouts of the criminals within the Bwari and Kwali. A security officer told PRNigeria a huge sum of money paid as ransoms were recovered. An investigation is ongoing.